article.headline: Colgate beats Binghamton 65-44
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Matt McMullen scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers, Luke Roh scored 14, and Colgate beat Binghamton 65-44 Wednesday night. Damon Sherman-Newsome and Pat Moore both scored 11 points, Austin Tillotson had 10 assists, and the Raiders (3-7) out-rebounded the Bearcats 33-30. Dusan Perovic scored 16 points for Binghamton (1-10), which shot 34.9 percent from the field and was hurt by 18 turnovers. Binghamton led briefly 6-5 on a layup by Nick Madray, but Colgate used a 9-2 run to pull ahead and led 24-13 after a 10-2 run in which Moore and McMullen each hit 3-pointers. McMullen scored eight points and Colgate led 26-16 at halftime. Colgate opened the second with an 8-2 run and led 57-33 at 6:45 after a 15-2 run in which McMullen scored seven points while the Bearcats went scoreless for more than 5 minutes. Binghamton finished with six unanswered points, but couldn't catch the Raiders.
